00:23:58,430 --> 00:24:01,630
你去跟萨特南联系
Let's get Satnam on the communications link.

359
00:24:01,660 --> 00:24:03,140
对比一下这些数据
Try to cross reference the data.

360
00:24:03,170 --> 00:24:06,330
这里是国家公园 不该有围栏吧?
It's a national park, there's not supposed to be fences, right?

361
00:24:06,470 --> 00:24:08,430
我的意思是 发生什么事了?
I mean, what's going on here?

362
00:24:08,460 --> 00:24:10,550
我们是地质学家
We're geologists.

363
00:24:10,970 --> 00:24:13,560
你们用机关枪挖地?
You usually go digging with machine guns?

364
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:16,940
少校 我来处理就好 谢谢!
Major, I'll take care of this, thank you.

365
00:24:16,970 --> 00:24:18,580
那个湖怎么了?
So, what happened to the lake?

366
00:24:18,610 --> 00:24:20,320
这正是我们要调查的
Well, that's what we're trying to find out.

367
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,550
我们发现这里变得很不稳定
We think the entire area has become unstable.

368
00:24:22,580 --> 00:24:24,340
你应该带着你的孩子离开这里 
I think you should take your kids and leave, Mr....

369
00:24:24,470 --> 00:24:26,030
柯蒂斯先生
Curtis.

370
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:32,160
你该不会就是《再见亚特兰蒂斯》的作者 杰克逊・柯蒂斯吧?
You're not by any chance the Jackson Curtis who wrote "Farewell Atlantis"?

371
00:24:34,450 --> 00:24:35,660
正是在下
The very same.

372
00:24:36,910 --> 00:24:39,630
那本书是献给我妈妈的
It's actually dedicated to my mom.

373
00:24:41,710 --> 00:24:45,590
我大学时读过一些你的短篇小说
I read a couple of your short stories in college.

374
00:24:45,620 --> 00:24:49,300
- 你爸爸是个很有才华的人 - 听到了吧
- Your father is a very, very talented man. - Listen up.

375
00:24:49,330 --> 00:24:51,310
真巧 我正在读你的书
It's amazing. I'm reading your book.

376
00:24:51,340 --> 00:24:54,530
看到第300天 太空船与地球失去了联系
I'm around day 300, the shuttle has just lost communication with Earth.

377
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,430
很少有人买这本书
You're one of the lucky few who bought it.

378
00:24:56,520 --> 00:24:58,690
- 我没买 - 没买?
- I didn't buy it. - No?

379
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:00,690
我老爸送我的
My dad gave it to me.

380
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,760
我想问你一些事
Let me ask you something.

381
00:25:04,190 --> 00:25:06,850
你真的相信在生死关头
Do you think those people would behave so selflessly

382
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:08,820
人们会那么无私吗?
knowing that their own lives were at stake?

383
00:25:08,860 --> 00:25:10,700
我希望是
I hope so.

384
00:25:10,740 --> 00:25:14,080
评论家说我太天真 是个幼稚的乐观主义者
The critics said I was naive, an unabashed optimist,

385
00:25:14,110 --> 00:25:15,790
可他们又懂什么呢 对吧?
but what do they know, right?

386
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:20,500
- 很荣幸认识你 - 我也是
- It was a great pleasure meeting you. - Thank you.

387
00:25:20,530 --> 00:25:23,170
少校 麻烦您把他们送到露营区
Mayor, could you escort these good people to the camp grounds, please.

388
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:24,570
- 这是你的 - 对
- This is yours. - Yeah.

389
00:25:24,670 --> 00:25:25,670
- 谢谢 - 是 长官
- Thank you. - Yes, sir.

390
00:25:25,710 --> 00:25:27,760
- 保重 - 好的
- Take care. - Okay

391
00:25:27,790 --> 00:25:28,810
他人不错
He was very nice.

392
00:25:28,840 --> 00:25:31,220
你这样说是因为他喜欢我的书吧
You're just saying that cause he likes my book.

393
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:39,990
看来你儿子会比我们都聪明
Looks like that boy of yours is gonna be smarter than any of us.

394
00:25:44,650 --> 00:25:45,950
怎么了?
What's wrong?

395
00:25:45,980 --> 00:25:49,030
我把温度数据发给他了
I sent Satnam the temperature readings.

396
00:25:49,070 --> 00:25:53,250
你的数据 与我在阿根廷和安大略的同事测到的数据 几乎一样
My colleagues in Argentina and Ontario have almost identical data.

397
00:25:53,280 --> 00:25:55,660
这里太热 我们只好把铜矿井封了
It's so hot here we've had to seal off the mine.

398
00:25:55,690 --> 00:25:58,500
- 你仔细检查过数据了吗? - 我检查了3遍 我的朋友
- Did you double check the numbers? - I triple checked, my friend.

399
00:25:58,950 --> 00:26:02,000
我希望是我们弄错了 但是 事实就是这样
I wish we were wrong, but, we're not.

400
00:26:03,290 --> 00:26:06,460
地壳越来越不稳定了
The Earth's crust is destabilizing.

401
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:15,850
- 这太快了 - 艾德里安 你们必须开始撤离了
- It's too early. - Adrian. You have to begin the evacuation.

402
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:19,360
天啊
My God.

403
00:26:19,390 --> 00:26:23,200
什么高科技 先进的设备
All our scientific advances, our fancy machines,

404
00:26:23,250 --> 00:26:26,000
玛雅人几千年前就预测到了
the Mayans saw this coming thousands of years ago.

405
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:37,700
我以为还有很多时间
I thought we'd have more time.

406
00:26:47,340 --> 00:26:49,670
好 我要你和家人赶快收拾行李
Okay, I want you to pack up your family.

407
00:26:49,710 --> 00:26:52,010
我会安排飞机到新德里接你们
I'm gonna arrange an airlift from Delhi.

408
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:54,050
谢谢你 我的朋友
Thank you, my friend.

409
00:26:54,090 --> 00:26:56,010
祝我们好运
And good luck.

410
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:06,310
阿吉特
Ajit.

411
00:27:07,270 --> 00:27:09,400
我们要去坐大船了
We are going on a big ship.

412
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,930
等等 等等 等一等
Wait. Wait, wait. Wait

413
00:27:21,990 --> 00:27:24,210
打扰了 就一个问题
Sorry. One question.

414
00:27:24,250 --> 00:27:29,200
政府的人跟你们说了什么?
What did the government guys say to you?

415
00:27:32,550 --> 00:27:35,340
说我们不该翻越围栏
They don't like us going over their fences and

416
00:27:35,380 --> 00:27:38,850
还说这整个区域很不稳定
that the whole area back there is unstable.

417
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:42,220
"不稳定"? 他们说"不稳定"?
"Unstable"? They said "unstable"?

418
00:27:45,190 --> 00:27:47,860
- 很好笑 哈哈哈 - 我们走
- That's funny. - Let's go.

419
00:27:51,610 --> 00:27:54,030
"不稳定" 哈哈哈
"Unstable".

420
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:00,670
不只是黄石公园 长官
It's not just Yellowstone, sir.

421
00:28:00,700 --> 00:28:03,800
全球所有热区的温度
Temperatures are rising with incredible velocity

422
00:28:03,830 --> 00:28:05,380
都在急剧上升
in hot zones across the globe.

423
00:28:05,410 --> 00:28:07,970
艾德里安 你百分之百的确定吗?
Are you absolutely sure about this, Adrian?

424
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:12,050
一旦命令发布 就无法撤销了 你明白的
Because once we give these orders, there's no going back. You understand that.

425
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:15,220
恐怕没有时间犹豫了 长官
I'm afraid there's no longer any doubt, sir.

426
00:28:15,250 --> 00:28:17,130
我们得尽可能的多救人
We have to save what we can.

427
00:28:17,170 --> 00:28:19,680
我们得马上撤离
And we have to move now!

428
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:47,200
黄 石 国 家 公 园
政府管制区

429
00:28:49,330 --> 00:28:53,590
这里好多蚊子 你没带防蚊液吗?
There's mosquitoes in here. Did anybody spray the tent?

430
00:28:53,620 --> 00:28:55,680
我明天就去买
I'm gonna get that spray tomorrow.

431
00:28:55,710 --> 00:28:58,590
蚊子喜欢你 是因为你的血太甜了
They just like you because your blood's so sweet.

432
00:28:59,390 --> 00:29:02,180
爹地 你说过不写书的
Dad, you said you wouldn't work on your book.

433
00:29:02,220 --> 00:29:03,100
什么?
What?

434
00:29:03,140 --> 00:29:06,310
我没写书 我在做别的事
I'm not, I'm not. I'm doing something else.

435
00:29:09,140 --> 00:29:10,690
好吧
Okay.

436
00:29:13,820 --> 00:29:15,650
你真需要这么多帽子吗?
Did you really need all these hats?

437
00:29:15,690 --> 00:29:17,030
你的那个东西呢?
Where are your pull-ups?

438
00:29:17,060 --> 00:29:18,610
我已经穿上了
I have them on.

439
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,530
谁给你的 妈妈?
Who gave you this? Mommy?

440
00:29:27,660 --> 00:29:30,120
不 这是戈登送我的生日礼物
No, Gordon gave it to me for my birthday.

441
00:29:30,670 --> 00:29:34,200
买手机应该经过家庭讨论吧
A cell phone is something we got to talk about. You know, as a family.

442
00:29:35,420 --> 00:29:37,420
什么家庭啊?
What family?

443
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:43,850
你这么说让我很伤心
It hurts my feelings when you say stuff like that.

444
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:56,320
大人也会伤心的
Adults get hurt feelings too.

445
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:56,220
嘿！戈登， 露营糟透了！

446
00:30:13,670 --> 00:30:15,040
不可能
No way.

447
00:30:15,460 --> 00:30:16,260
你是唯一敢说出真相的人
You're brave to tell the truth.

448
00:30:16,300 --> 00:30:18,390
谢谢你 比尔 你有什么问题?
Thank you, Bill. What is your question?

449
00:30:18,420 --> 00:30:21,180
我想知道这一切会从哪里开始?
I wanted to know, where is all this gonna start?

450
00:30:21,220 --> 00:30:24,200
一般这都是好莱坞的好戏
Well, something like this could only originate in Hollywood Bill.

451
00:30:24,230 --> 00:30:27,180
不过说真的 加州的地面已经在开裂了
But, they have the earth cracking under their asses already.

452
00:30:27,220 --> 00:30:30,500
我们全家都信仰耶稣
Our family believes in the gospel of the lord Jesus.

453
00:30:30,560 --> 00:30:31,820
我们无所畏惧 查理
We have nothing to fear, Charlie.

454
00:30:31,850 --> 00:30:33,820
那太好了 比尔 感谢你的来电
Good for you, Bill. Thanks for calling.

455
00:30:33,930 --> 00:30:38,900
我是查理・弗罗斯特 在黄石公园为您现场直播
This is Charlie Frost reporting live from Yellowstone National Park,

456
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:44,300
这里马上将成为世界上最大的活火山
soon to become the world's largest active volcano.

457
00:30:44,490 --> 00:30:46,620
朋友们 马上回来
I'll be right back, folks.

458
00:30:48,950 --> 00:30:50,660
介意我打扰下吗?
Do you mind if I join you?

459
00:30:50,700 --> 00:30:52,370
我想问你点事
I wanted to ask you something.

460
00:30:52,580 --> 00:30:56,340
我时间不多 吃泡菜吗?
I only got a minute. Pickle?

461
00:30:56,790 --> 00:30:57,540
不了
No

462
00:30:57,890 --> 00:31:00,260
我刚在收听你的节目 我好奇的是
I was listening to the broadcast and I was wondering

463
00:31:00,300 --> 00:31:03,980
到底是什么会从好莱坞开始?
what exactly is it that's gonna start in Hollywood?

464
00:31:04,010 --> 00:31:08,060
是末世 世界末日
It's the Apocalypse. End of days.

465
00:31:08,110 --> 00:31:11,730
审判日 世界末日 我的朋友
The Judgment Day. The end of the world, my friend.

466
00:31:11,780 --> 00:31:15,100
基督徒称之为"被提时刻" 但玛雅人很早就预言了
Christians call it The Rapture, but the Mayans knew about it.

467
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:21,540
霍皮人 易经 圣经也都说过
The Hopis, the I Ching, the Bible, kind of.

468
00:31:21,790 --> 00:31:24,410
- 要啤酒吗? - 好
- Beer? - Yeah.

469
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:26,170
你看 我得吃饭了
So look, I gotta eat.

470
00:31:26,210 --> 00:31:28,970
你何不到我的博客里下载呢?
Why don't you download my blog?

471
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:33,710
免费的 当然我们也欢迎捐款
It's free. Of course, we do appreciate donations.

472
00:31:33,760 --> 00:31:37,900
数千年前 玛雅文明最先发现
In ancient times, the Mayan people were the first civilization to discover that

473
00:31:37,940 --> 00:31:40,100
地球是有期限的
this planet had an expiration date.

474
00:31:40,150 --> 00:31:45,900
根据他们的历法 2012年将会有毁灭性的灾难降临
According to their calender, in the year 2012 a cataclysmic event will unfold,

475
00:31:45,930 --> 00:31:48,900
因为太阳系的全部行星排成一条直线
caused by an alignment of the planets in our solar system

476
00:31:48,940 --> 00:31:53,280
这种现象每64万年才发生一次
that only happens every 640,000 years.

477
00:31:53,310 --> 00:31:54,910
噢 别又来了
Oh, not again.

478
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:59,280
不错吧? 这动画都是我自己做的
Neat, huh? I did all the animation myself.

479
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:02,990
把地球想象成一个橙子
Just imagine the earth as an orange.

480
00:32:03,030 --> 00:32:05,430
先用幽默吸引他们
You lure them in with humor.

481
00:32:05,660 --> 00:32:07,590
然后让他们去思考
Then you make them think.

482
00:32:07,620 --> 00:32:11,080
太阳将释放出大量的射线
Our sun will begin to emit such extreme amounts of radiation,

483
00:32:11,130 --> 00:32:13,510
钉死你个浑蛋 来点中微子吧
Screw you bastards. Do you call neutrinos?

484
00:32:13,550 --> 00:32:17,250
首先 地心开始熔化
That the core of the earth will melt at the inside part of the orange.

485
00:32:17,300 --> 00:32:20,270
然后地壳就可以自由移动
Leaving the crust of our planet free to shift.

486
00:32:20,300 --> 00:32:25,500
1958年 查尔斯・哈普古德教授 将此理论命名为 "地壳漂移"
In 1958 Professor Charles Hapgood named it:"Earth Crust Displacement".

487
00:32:25,550 --> 00:32:28,570
阿尔伯特・爱因斯坦也支持这个理论
Albert Einstein did support it.

488
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:29,900
人类将完全感受到
People will get it all.

489
00:32:29,950 --> 00:32:32,900
地球母亲的毁灭性力量
The forces of Mother Nature will be so devastating.

490
00:32:32,950 --> 00:32:39,070
世界末日就在2012年12月21日冬至那天
It will bring an end to this world on winter Solstice 12-21-12.

491
00:32:39,110 --> 00:32:43,450
听众们要记住 是查理・弗罗斯特最先告诉你们的
Always remember, folks. You heard it first from Charlie Frost.

492
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:47,250
政府会想法设法保守这个秘密
You'd have to keep a thing like this under wraps.

493
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:48,830
道理很简单
I mean, just think about it.

494
00:32:48,960 --> 00:32:51,830
首先 股市会崩盘
First, the stock market would go.

495
00:32:51,870 --> 00:32:54,210
然后 经济崩溃 嘣!
Then the economy: Boom!

496
00:32:54,250 --> 00:32:55,460
美元狂跌 嘣!
The dollar: Boom!

497
00:32:55,500 --> 00:32:57,760
还有街头骚乱
And then pandemonium in the street.

498
00:32:57,790 --> 00:33:01,680
战争 种族灭绝 嘣! 嘣! 嘣!
War, genocide. Boom! Boom! Boom!

499
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:05,100
胡说 没人能守得住这么大的秘密 查理
Bullshit. Nobody could keep that big a secret, Charlie.

500
00:33:05,130 --> 00:33:06,100
一定会有人说出来的
Somebody would blow the whistle

501
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:10,020
没错 每过一段时间就会有可怜虫想说出来
An every once in a while, some poor little sucker tries.

502
00:33:10,050 --> 00:33:12,610
就像这些家伙 嘣! 嘣!
Like these guys. Boom! Boom!

503
00:33:12,650 --> 00:33:16,610
所有这些人 死了! 死了! 死了!
Every one of these guys. Dead! Dead! Dead!

504
00:33:18,240 --> 00:33:21,740
等等 这是梅耶教授
Woah, that's Professor Meyers.

505
00:33:21,780 --> 00:33:25,200
他负责亚特兰蒂斯宇宙飞船计划 你认识他?
He ran the Atlantis Shuttle Program. Did you know him?

506
00:33:25,250 --> 00:33:27,040
对 写书时他帮了我很多
Yeah, he helped me out with research on my book.

507
00:33:27,070 --> 00:33:30,580
那一定是在他出事之前
Well, that must have been before his accident.

508
00:33:30,610 --> 00:33:34,080
- 梅耶教授死了? - 对 两个月前
- Meyers is dead? - Yeah, two months ago.

509
00:33:34,130 --> 00:33:37,630
他是我的狂热听众之一
He was one of my most avid listeners.

510
00:33:37,660 --> 00:33:39,200
他全都弄清楚了
He had it all figured out.

511
00:33:39,230 --> 00:33:42,760
政府在做什么 怎么做 在哪里
Everything the government was doing, where, why.

512
00:33:42,790 --> 00:33:45,760
他甚至寄给我一张地图
He even sent me a map.

513
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:48,810
什么地图 查理? 什么地图? 
A map for what, Charlie? What's the map for?

514
00:33:55,150 --> 00:34:00,400
他们在造太空船 伙计
They're building space ships, man.

515
00:34:05,320 --> 00:34:11,330
胡扯 我得走了 我要回地球去了
Shit, man, I have to go. Because, I gotta get back to Earth.

516
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:14,120
- 你还有啤酒吗? - 这是最后一罐
- Do you have a beer? - This is my last.

517
00:34:14,160 --> 00:34:17,740
好吧 我真是大开眼界了
Alright, anyway, I really enjoyed most of this.

518
00:34:17,800 --> 00:34:19,100
非常感谢你
Thank you so much.

519
00:34:20,260 --> 00:34:22,220
知道吗? 他们在卖座位!
Guess what, they're selling seats!

520
00:34:22,250 --> 00:34:23,220
给我留三张
Put me down for three.

521
00:34:23,260 --> 00:34:25,770
不可能 像我们这种普通人是没有机会的
No! Guys like you and me don't have any chance.

522
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:31,100
除非是你比尔・盖茨 默多克 或者俄罗斯的亿万富翁才行
You'd have to be Bill Gates or Rupert Murdoch, or some Russian billionaire.

523
00:34:31,130 --> 00:34:32,610
小点声 我的孩子睡着了
Keep it down, my kids are sleeping.

